      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your worth isn't reflected in your weakness, and expecting them to carry you will only bring them more stress. Besides their parents, what are they going to do? You're a parent, and being a parent means letting go sometimes. There's no use pretending to be perfect; they can see right through it. Your value lies in the memories you've made, the sacrifices you've made, and the lessons you've taught them - not in your physical strength or ability to care for yourself.",
